## Appendix B. Pre-Submission Checklist
- [ ] The objective is stated in one precise sentence and matches the assignment scope.
- [ ] Key parameters are explicit: audience, constraints, inputs, exclusions, and assumptions.
- [ ] The required result is measurable and formatted for evaluation.
- [ ] The method is sequenced and includes correction or validation behavior where needed.
- [ ] Required tools or sources are declared; prohibited tools are excluded.
- [ ] The file is named correctly and versioned.
- [ ] The submission is readable, organized, and free from unsupported claims.
- [ ] Supporting evidence is attached when the task requires tests, outputs, or rationale.

## Appendix C. Core Glossary
| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| Objective | The explicit target the prompt or system is intended to achieve. |
| Parameters | Constraints, inputs, conditions, variables, exclusions, and operating limits. |
| Results | The required output form, quality level, acceptance criteria, and expected deliverable state. |
| Method | The ordered process the system should follow to generate or validate the output. |
| Tools | Models, sources, files, automations, or external systems allowed or required for execution. |
| Compliance | Conformance to defined structure, rules, standards, and assignment requirements. |
| Capstone | The final integrated project used to verify end-to-end certification readiness. |
| Version Control | The practice of tracking revisions so the current approved artifact can be identified and audited. |
